('b0daa6c9-990f-4b52-989e-3ec5a6771fe1', 'Beam Dream: The Trendy Sleep Ritual', 'Beam Dream has taken social media by storm as a delicious bedtime ritual. The combination of nano hemp, reishi, magnesium, and L-theanine creates a relaxing pre-sleep experience.', 'Nano hemp extract for relaxation. Reishi mushroom for stress. Magnesium for muscle relaxation. L-Theanine for calm focus. Low-dose melatonin (3mg).', ARRAY['Delicious dessert flavors', 'Enjoyable bedtime ritual', 'Multi-ingredient formula', 'Popular and well-reviewed'], 'Mix 1 scoop with warm water or milk 30 minutes before bed. The ritual of making the drink enhances relaxation.', ARRAY['Contains hemp/CBD extract', 'Expensive per serving', 'Added sweeteners', 'Proprietary blend amounts'], 'Social media-savvy wellness consumers who want an enjoyable bedtime ritual with sleep-supporting ingredients.', 'Natrol Sleep Support for more clinical formula. Magnesium Glycinate for simple approach.', 'Q: Will the CBD show on a drug test? A: The nano hemp extract contains trace THC which could theoretically trigger a test. Q: Is the hot cocoa flavor good? A: It is genuinely delicious and the ritual of making it helps you wind down.', 8.2, '[{"name": "Sophia K.", "rating": 5, "text": "The hot cocoa flavor is amazing. Making this drink has become my favorite bedtime ritual.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-13"}, {"name": "Ben A.", "rating": 4, "text": "Pricey but the relaxation effect is real. I fall asleep faster and the taste makes me look forward to bedtime.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-24"}]'::jsonb),

('213921ad-ac46-4bdd-b54e-2bb2d694016d', 'OLLY Sleep Gummies: Candy That Helps You Sleep', 'OLLY made sleep supplements fun with blackberry-flavored gummies that taste like candy. Gentle formula with low-dose melatonin and calming botanicals.', 'Melatonin at a gentle 3mg dose. L-Theanine for relaxation without drowsiness. Chamomile, passionflower, and lemon balm for herbal calming support.', ARRAY['Tastes like candy', 'Very affordable', 'Gentle low-dose melatonin', 'Available everywhere'], 'Take 2 gummies 30 minutes before bed. Do not exceed recommended dose.', ARRAY['Contains added sugar', 'Lower ingredient doses than capsules', 'Gummy format is less precise', 'Not for those avoiding sweeteners'], 'Casual users who want a tasty, easy, gentle sleep aid without swallowing pills.', 'Melatonin capsules for more precise dosing. Natrol for comprehensive formula.', 'Q: Are gummies less effective than capsules? A: They contain less active ingredient per serving but the compliance is higher since people enjoy taking them. Q: Can kids take them? A: Consult a pediatrician. These are formulated for adults.', 7.6, '[{"name": "Chelsea R.", "rating": 4, "text": "My whole family uses these. They taste so good and help me fall asleep gently.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-04"}, {"name": "Derek M.", "rating": 4, "text": "Great for occasional sleep issues. Not strong enough for serious insomnia but perfect for winding down.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-20"}]'::jsonb),

('3fea9260-3813-4791-bdc2-f2856ec92134', 'Magtein: Brain-Targeted Magnesium for Sleep', 'The only magnesium form clinically shown to cross the blood-brain barrier. Developed at MIT for cognitive function, it has become a sleep staple.', 'Magnesium L-Threonate (Magtein) was developed at MIT and is patented. It significantly increases brain magnesium levels, which decline with age and affect sleep and cognition.', ARRAY['Crosses blood-brain barrier', 'MIT-developed and patented', 'Supports both sleep and cognition', 'Well-tolerated'], 'Take 3 capsules in the evening, 1-2 hours before bed.', ARRAY['3 capsules per serving', 'Lower elemental magnesium per dose', 'More expensive than other magnesium forms'], 'Those wanting brain-targeted magnesium for both cognitive benefits and improved sleep quality.', 'Magnesium Glycinate for general relaxation. Apigenin for non-mineral approach.', 'Q: Is Magtein better than glycinate for sleep? A: Different mechanisms. Magtein targets brain magnesium levels while glycinate provides systemic relaxation. Both are effective. Q: Can I combine them? A: Yes, they work through different pathways.', 8.4, '[{"name": "Dr. Alan C.", "rating": 5, "text": "The research behind Magtein is compelling. I take it nightly and recommend it to patients for both sleep and cognitive support.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-10"}, {"name": "Karen L.", "rating": 4, "text": "Noticeable improvement in both sleep quality and daytime mental clarity after 2 weeks.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-22"}]'::jsonb),

('704bfe5e-737a-41b6-8430-c0f62d7603b4', 'Apigenin: The Huberman Sleep Pick', 'Popularized by neuroscientist Andrew Huberman, apigenin is the active compound in chamomile that promotes relaxation. A clean single-ingredient approach to better sleep.', 'Apigenin 50mg is a concentrated form of the flavonoid found in chamomile tea. At this dose, it provides significantly more than you could get from drinking tea.', ARRAY['Science-backed single ingredient', 'Popularized by Dr. Huberman', 'Non-hormonal sleep support', 'Great for stacking'], 'Take 1 capsule 30-60 minutes before bed. Can be combined with magnesium and theanine.', ARRAY['Subtle effects for some users', 'Single ingredient only', 'May lower estrogen (caution for women)', 'Limited long-term studies at this dose'], 'Biohackers following the Huberman sleep stack protocol and those wanting non-hormonal sleep support.', 'Magnesium L-Threonate for brain-targeted support. Glycine for amino acid approach.', 'Q: What is the Huberman sleep stack? A: Apigenin 50mg, magnesium L-threonate, and L-theanine taken 30-60 minutes before bed. Q: Is 50mg a lot? A: It is equivalent to drinking many cups of chamomile tea in concentrated form.', 7.8, '[{"name": "Matt H.", "rating": 4, "text": "Part of my Huberman sleep stack. Combined with mag and theanine, my sleep is the best it has ever been.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-09"}, {"name": "Jenny S.", "rating": 4, "text": "Subtle on its own but effective as part of a stack. I appreciate the clean single ingredient.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-17"}]'::jsonb),

('64bc0b79-d161-452e-87a9-2a104f27928d', 'Sleep Breakthrough: Premium Sleep Drink', 'A comprehensive drink powder targeting every sleep stage. Premium formula with bioavailable magnesium, amino acids, and botanicals for deep restorative sleep.', 'Magnesium bisglycinate for muscle relaxation. Glycine and GABA for neurotransmitter support. PharmaGABA for calming. L-Theanine for alpha waves. Tart cherry for natural melatonin.', ARRAY['Comprehensive multi-pathway formula', 'Delicious drink format', 'No melatonin dependency', 'Targets all sleep stages'], 'Mix 1 scoop with 8 oz cold water 30 minutes before bed.', ARRAY['Premium pricing', 'Large serving size', 'Only available online', 'Some proprietary blend amounts'], 'Those who prefer a drink format and want a comprehensive formula without relying on melatonin.', 'Beam Dream for trending option. Natrol Sleep for capsule formula.', 'Q: Why no melatonin? A: It uses tart cherry which provides natural melatonin precursors without the dependency risk of synthetic melatonin. Q: How does the drink format compare? A: Liquid delivery allows faster absorption than capsules.', 8.2, '[{"name": "Andrea M.", "rating": 5, "text": "Best sleep product I have used. The drink format is so much better than swallowing pills before bed.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-07"}, {"name": "Craig P.", "rating": 4, "text": "Expensive but effective. I sleep through the night now and wake up feeling genuinely refreshed.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-19"}]'::jsonb),

('47ba37e2-f7af-4efd-bb7f-373002d5eddb', 'Tru Niagen: The Most Studied NAD+ Booster', 'Tru Niagen has the most published clinical trials of any NR supplement. FDA GRAS status and clinically proven to increase NAD+ levels by up to 51%.', 'Nicotinamide Riboside (Niagen) at 300mg is the only NR with an FDA new dietary ingredient notification and multiple published human clinical trials.', ARRAY['Multiple published clinical trials', 'FDA GRAS status', 'Clinically shown to boost NAD+ 51%', 'Simple one-capsule dose'], 'Take 1 capsule (300mg) daily with or without food. Consistent daily use recommended.', ARRAY['Expensive for a single ingredient', 'Effects hard to feel immediately', 'Requires ongoing supplementation'], 'Longevity-focused adults who want the most researched and validated NAD+ boosting supplement.', 'Basis by Elysium for NR with pterostilbene. CoQ10 for mitochondrial support.', 'Q: Tru Niagen vs Basis? A: Both contain NR. Tru Niagen is pure NR while Basis adds pterostilbene. Tru Niagen has more published trials. Q: How do I know it is working? A: Blood tests can confirm NAD+ level increases.', 8.8, '[{"name": "Dr. James L.", "rating": 5, "text": "I recommend Tru Niagen to my patients. The clinical evidence and FDA GRAS status give me confidence in the product.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-11"}, {"name": "Sandra T.", "rating": 4, "text": "Cannot feel the effects directly but my blood work shows improved NAD+ levels after 3 months.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-23"}]'::jsonb),

